About this item

  • 6-way Extension Lead with 2m cable H05VV-F 3G1,25 protection against contact - provides even more safety
  • Extension Lead protects valuable devices from electrical surges with a maximum leakage current of up to 13,500 A (protection during electrical storms, lightning strikes, etc.)
  • Extension Cord with illuminated safety switch for turning on and off and neon indicator
  • Power Strip in a slim design with practical keywholes for wall mounting
  • 6-way Extension Cable ideal for use at home or in the office to provide power to connected devices

From the manufacturer

6-way Extension Lead

6-way Extension Cable ideal for use at home or in the office to provide power to connected devices.

Meaning of the neon indicators

The red neon indicator shows that the surge protection is active with a maximum leakage current of up to 13500A - The green neon indicator shows that the protective earth conductor is correctly connected.

Wall mounting option

Power Strip in a slim design with practical keywholes for wall mounting.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    R. F. Stevens
    5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent well-made six-way extension strip with surge dumping.
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 2 November 2023
    Style Name: 6-wayVerified Purchase
    The 2metre Brennenstuhl six gang extension lead with surge-protection is well made and has good contacts, perfect for UK homes and businesses. The Az-blurb is accurate.

    It expects to be plugged into a normal well maintained 13A socket with a good earth, and not an extension lead.

    It is a welcome improvement over some generic anonymous on-line offerings Ive tried recently and immediately binned because they were potentially lethal.

    I took a look inside. It has a decent thickness of buss conductors with contacts that grip plug-pins properly and will last. The surge protection is in a neat little circuit board located near the input lead and mains switch.

    The mains switch isolates the whole of the strip including the surge protection board from the incoming live line. The neutral is always connected, as is the earth.

    The cover is secured by tamper-resistant screws; however, with the correct tools access is possible to enable a safety check.

    The 13A plug is moulded in the correct shape with safe pins and contained the correct fuse.
